                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2444: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-30T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 30, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Substance of your September 29, 5 p.m.,<note n="18" xml:id="d480fn18">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_490">p. 490</ref>.</note> has
                    been repeated to London and Paris for information and for such discreet use as
                    Ambassadors may deem judicious in furtherance of effort to expedite a favorable
                    decision by the British and French Governments.</p>
                <p>What has been or is being done with reference to the currency loan option held by
                    old consortium which expires October 11?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
